data.title: Marines TV
data.meta_description:
U.S. Marine Corps 2nd Lt. Nkundimana Claude, a fire team leader assigned to Alpha Company, 1st Battalion, 23rd Marine Regiment, 4th Marine Division, speaks on his journey to commissioning as a second lieutenant at Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, California, June 9, 2023. Claude moved to the U.S. from Democratic Republic of Congo, Africa, and enlisted in the Marine Corps to become a U.S. citizen. He then graduated from Texas State University and commissioned as an officer. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. James Stanfield)
